text: Last week, I joined our health care providers at @BonSecours to hear about the incredible work they’re doing to provide attentive and accessible medical care to Americans in the Commonwealth of Virginia. We discussed the strategic investments in the Rural Health Transformation Program in the Working Families Tax Cut as well as my recent work to keep insurance premiums low for the middle-class in my bipartisan Premium Tax Credit Extension Act. Access to quality, affordable health insurance is crucial and as a geriatric nurse practitioner, it dictates how I choose to legislate for #VA02.

Last week, I joined public health officials, medical experts, and my colleagues in @ProbSolveCaucus for a roundtable discussion in recognition of National Recovery Month. We discussed the links between mental health and substance use as well as the barriers to treatment. We are working on bipartisan legislation to address these treatment obstacles and focus on prevention of substance abuse.

Thank you to everyone who stopped by our Mobile Office Hours in Windsor, VA..!! Whether you had questions about a VA claim, needed help with a passport, or just wanted to share your thoughts—my team was glad to connect with you. Stay tuned for details on future Mobile Office Hours..!!

Last week, we had some special visitors in Washington, DC… I met with students from the @AIPAC Student Leadership Summit, @PalantirTech, @TheUSONetwork, @amgoldstarfam, and the Asian-American Hotel Owners Association. I was also honored to receive the “Champion: Protecting America’s Warfighters” Award from the American Biodefense Action Coalition, and capped off the week at Pet Night on Capitol Hill! It was a busy and productive week for sure….!

This week in Washington, we helped assemble over 2,000 toiletry care packages for deployed servicemembers stationed around the world. I’m grateful to everyone who volunteered their time to support our men and women in uniform—these small reminders from home mean so much to those serving abroad. Thank you to the @The_USO for sponsoring the event…! 🇺🇸

Happy National Clean Energy Week! I was excited to spend time at the National Clean Energy Week Policy Symposium to hear from business leaders, stakeholders, and policymakers on how to unleash the free market to create jobs, remain energy independent, and preserve our environment..!

Today, I voted to keep the government open. While a continuing resolution isn’t ideal, it gives us the time we need to finish the responsible work of passing appropriations bills—something the House has already made real progress on. I’ll keep fighting to restore fiscal discipline and ensure Congress respects the hard-earned tax dollars of the American people.

Today, on National POW/MIA Recognition Day, we pause to honor the brave Americans who endured captivity in service to our nation and those who never returned home. Our nation is forever indebted to these heroes. May we honor their courage, pray for their loved ones, and remain committed to bringing every service member home. You are not forgotten.

While Congress continues its work to fund the government and avoid a harmful shutdown, we must be prepared. My bill, the Pay Our Troops Act of 2026, ensures that members of the U.S. Armed Forces, including the Coast Guard, continue receiving pay and benefits in the event of a lapse in government funding.

I am horrified by the assassination of Charlie Kirk today. Charlie was more than a political activist—he was a fierce advocate for freedom of speech and a relentless defender of civilized political debate. Charlie challenged the younger generation and students on college campuses to understand commonsense conservatism and why it matters in leadership. My prayers are with his family and loved ones. May justice be served, and may God heal the deep political divide in our nation.

I am praying for Charlie Kirk. This disgusting act of violence is abhorrent, and the individual responsible must be prosecuted to the fullest extent of the law. Political violence is absolutely unacceptable.

From day one I have been committed to doing whatever I can to avoid a government shutdown and ensure our troops get paid no matter how bad Washington’s dysfunction may be. While the process to get here was unbelievably frustrating, I am relieved Congress found a bipartisan path forward tonight to keep the government open and accountable to the American people. As we work to return to regular order and pass full-year appropriations bills, I am proud to have fought hard to ensure this temporary funding bill included critical support for our defense industrial base that will help provide job stability for workers in Hampton Roads.

For over a year, I've led the fight to ensure paychecks for our troops in the case of a government shutdown. Our servicemembers and their families should not suffer because of Washington's dysfunction. My Pay Our Troops Act would ensure the military and Coast Guard will always receive their due pay. With a shutdown hours away, it’s time to bring this bipartisan bill to the House floor for a vote…!

Washington’s dysfunction is putting us on a path toward a govt shutdown. Unless we pass funding by midnight, our military and Coast Guard will go without pay. That is unacceptable to me! Congress must pass my Pay Our Troops Act to ensure our servicemembers get their paychecks!

I just voted to keep the government open and accountable to the American people. #VA02 would be devastated by a government shutdown and while the process hasn’t been pretty, I am disappointed that my colleagues on the other side of the aisle refused to come together at the 11th hour and find a path forward.

In addition to preventing a shutdown through March 14, 2025, this proposal would have also:
✅ Provided essential funding to support our local submarine manufacturing capabilities,
✅ Extended the Farm Bill through the end of FY25, giving critical support to our farmers
✅ Given much-needed disaster relief to Americans, specifically Virginians, affected by recent hurricanes.

I remain committed to working with my colleagues to fund our government and keep our military paid, especially during this holiday season.
